Preceding respiratory infection predisposing for primary and secondary invasive Haemophilus influenzae type b disease. Cases (117) with invasive Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) disease and their family members reported symptoms of respiratory infection during the 4-week period before the onset of Hib disease significantly more often than age-, sex- and residence-matched controls (225) and their family members during the same time period. Viral (adenovirus influenza A and B